item.title: Albion Online | MMO Fishing Games
item.description: Albion Online features a full fishing skill line including rods and bait for freshwater and saltwater fish, a timing-based casting and reeling minigame, fishing yield buffs from pies, and crafted meals to enhance success rates.

item.title: ArcheAge | MMO Fishing Games
item.description: ArcheAge offers both bait fishing and sports fishing—craft rods and bait, cast in open water, and even deep-sea rod fishing from a rowboat or yacht.

item.title: Black Desert Online | MMO Fishing Games
item.description: Black Desert Online's fishing is a real-time minigame with timers, equipment upgrades, and ocean-depth exploration for rare catches.

item.title: Final Fantasy XI | MMO Fishing Games
item.description: FFXI’s Fishing profession uses rods, bait, and timing-based minigames; certain fish drops are used in crafting and achievements.

item.title: Final Fantasy XIV | MMO Fishing Games
item.description: Final Fantasy XIV features a deep fishing system with multiple bait types, fish logs, catch-and-release events, and seasonal fishing tournaments.

item.title: Guild Wars 2 | MMO Fishing Games
item.description: Guild Wars 2 includes fishing in open-world lakes and rivers with collectible fish, crafting ingredients, and achievements.

item.title: RuneScape | MMO Fishing Games
item.description: RuneScape offers both free and members-only fishing areas, a Fishing skill for XP, and special lakes for high-level anglers.

item.title: The Elder Scrolls Online | MMO Fishing Games
item.description: ESO includes a full Fishing skill—catch trophy fish, farm Perfect Roe for provisioning, and use Psijic buffs to improve catch rates.
